metadata.name: NAZCA #35
metadata.description:
Real time animation (WebGL)
Variable dimension
2022

Nazca is a group of living glyphs made in the soil of the GPU. There are 17 figures that get combined and mixed over three layers. The figures vary in complexity but are generally created with vertical and horizontal lines only. Figures have at least one seed, some even have a seed per path. A seed is an oscillating pixel that can be compared to a square wave oscillator of audio synthesis and is usually followed by a path or a set of paths. The purpose of the paths is to send the pixels along the lines to make the figures visible through movement and to create a reduction to pure animation.

metadata.name: Ersbla #393
metadata.description:
Ersbla is part of the fxhash live minting experience at Proof of People, London 2022. 

It is the third entry in a series of abstract generative experiments inspired by the graphic and textile work of Anni and Josef Albers. As a follow-up to the 'Sabler' and 'Lebras' collections, 'Ersbla' produces textile effects using a combination of thousands of tiny dots arranged on variable grids, resulting in a wide variety of unique Bauhaus-inspired compositions in a variety of palettes.

Press 'S' to save a high-resolution 2400 x 3396 px image in PNG format.

Depending on the density of your output, please allow up to a few seconds for your edition to generate.

metadata.name: Shapes of the civilization #50
metadata.description:
In my first generative work, I put together two things about myself: my past and my present/future.
I combine my past as a construction worker, with more than a decade of experience, with my current present of 5 years, as a multimedia artist.

It took me a long time to build this project, there were countless restarts until I finally found the path I wanted to follow.
As a multimedia artist I always like to learn new techniques, and when I discovered fxhash I had no doubts, I wanted to learn creative coding, and this is the result of my work and dedication.

I used elements of architecture mixed with my greatest passion (and also where I spent most of my time until I delve into programming), oil painting!
The color palettes were inspired by some painters I admire, making this work even more special and personal.

In live mode: Press 's' to save as PNG (4800x4800)

Made with p5js and love.
May-June 2022

NFT License 2.0

metadata.name: G. Masi #24
metadata.description:
45 years ago on May 12th, 1977 an 18 years old student was killed in Rome during a demonstration celebrating three years since the divorce referendum. As of today, no one has been found guilty for firing that bullet. Her name was Giorgiana Masi and her death shook the public opinion of the time.

45 years ago a close friend of my family, an artist that made a living with another job, created a painting that still hangs in my parent's living room and that has inspired me to seek art in all its forms. That painting represents an abstract human figure trapped in cage that takes a bullet while on the street.

This project is my digital reinterpretation of that painting and a thank you present to the first 45 among the holders of my other projects that will want to mint it.

- S key saves a PNG

metadata.name: Ries #104
metadata.description:
Ries is 500 sheets of paper. 
Ries is an cut-up text-artwork.
Ries is artwork generated by an algorithm based on seeded random numbers.
Ries is a digital artwork installed in 5 forms in exhibitions setting.
Ries is an NFT artwork. 

Ries is an artwork where I try bring together my experience of doing gallery exhibitions, my love for generative and copy machine art, DIY-punk aesthetics, NFT‚Äôs and chaos. 

The edition of Ries will be installed in different forms and collages in a gallery exhibition in Walden Kunstaustellungen in Berlin in July of 2022. Opening is at 8.7. 19.00, welcome if you are in Berlin.
/www.galerie-walden.de/

The seed idea for the project was the method of cut-up where a text (or something else) is cut into pieces and then rearranged to form something new. A modified Markov‚Äôs Chain algorithm makes a small text or a group of words from a pool of texts that include Art texts about cut up technique and generative art talk from tweets. These words form a visual bottom layer and then another layer of words samples the first, cutting it up and thus following the theme of the artwork.

Since the single iterations of the project are designed to be used in a collage, they come in various tone, density, detail and scale. One can test from the variations button and get a sense of what the generator produces. 

Controls in live view:
-Pressing  j exports the current image as jpeg
-Pressing  p  exports the current image as png

To change the detail level one can access the pixel density of render by adding ?pixDens=4 to the end of the URL in live view. You can of course you any number other than 4 also. I it renders just a black image, you have to lower the number, since it is then too large for WEBGL to render.

Designed to be best rendered on desktop Chrome.

Pricing info
22 tez - Includes a gallery shown, signed print sent to minter by mail or by telefax(!)
11 tez - A fair price for an artwork, also the minter can personally pick up a signed gallery shown print from the gallery, after the exhibition.
5 tez - 1/2 fair price
2 tez - bottom dollar

If you minted on lower tiers and would want a print, please contact the artist per twitter dm to ‚Äúupgrade‚Äù. If you bought secondary, and would want a print, please contact the artist per twitter dm.

Features exist mostly to help with artwork pairing for the collectors.


Markov‚Äôs chain code core is based on Markov Me! By https://codepen.io/alexkramerbanjo , MIT License

Displacement shader based on the wonderful shader examples by Adam Ferris


The artist holds the right to use the whole edition of Ries for display purposes for future exhibitions without asking permission or notifying the owners of the NFT‚Äôs.

1.7.2022 in Berlin
